ferite-serial
------------------------------------------
This is a Ferite serial interface module. Currently it only supports BSD
termios but the API is designed to be generic enough to support other serial
port systems without needing to change the API too dramatically.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libferite1-1.1.17-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libferite-devel-1.1.17-1bl1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/ferite/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/ferite/serial-ferite-module-1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ferite-serial-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ferite-serial-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ferite-serial-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ferite-serial-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ferite-serial)
  /usr/lib/ferite/module-descriptions/serial.xml
  /usr/lib/ferite/module-native/serial.dll
  /usr/lib/ferite/module-source/serial.fec
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ferite-serial.README
  /usr/share/doc/ferite-serial/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ferite-serial/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/ferite-serial/README
  /usr/share/doc/ferite/examples/serial/test.fe

------------------

